---
title: Close
---

p.-text Use a dismiss button with the class <code>a-close</code> to use in components who need to hide the information
  |  ( alerts, modals, etc).

.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    button(class='a-close',aria-label='Close')
  :code(lang="html")
    <button class="a-close" aria-label="Close"></button>

h3 Examples

h4 In Alerts
p.-text A button can be added to allow the user to dismiss the alert.
.example.-mb3
  .-p1
    .m-alert.-bubble.-warning.-hasIcon.-m2(data-title="Warning")
      | This is a warning alert
      button(class='a-close',aria-label='Close')
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="m-alert -warning -hasIcon" data-title="Warning" role="alert">
      This is a warning alert
      <button class="a-close" aria-label="Close"></button>
    </div>

h4 In Modals
.example.-mb3
  .a-modal__backdrop.-p6(style="position:relative;border-top-left-radius:3px;border-top-right-radius:3px;")
    .a-modal(style="margin-top:0;")
      .a-modal__header
        h3.a-modal__title Modal Title
        button.a-close(aria-label='Close')
      .a-modal__content
        p.-text.-m0 Modal content
      .a-modal__footer
        button.a-btn Cancel
        button.a-btn.-brand.-ml2 Save
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="a-modal__backdrop">
      <div class="a-modal">
        <div class="a-modal__header">
          <h3 class="a-modal__title">Modal Title</h3>
          <button class="a-close" aria-label="Close"></button>
        </div>
        <div class="a-modal__content">
          <p class="-text -m0">Modal content</p>
        </div>
        <div class="a-modal__footer">
          <button class="a-btn">Cancel</button>
          <button class="a-btn -brand -ml2">Save</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
